               <sense xml:id="Dmain" xml:lang="la" source="#dillmann"> <gramGrp> <pos expand="Substantivum">subst.</pos> </gramGrp> [i.q. <foreign xml:lang="ar">رُخَامٌ</foreign>] <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> marmor </quote></cit>: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ንፍቀ፡ ርኳም፡</foreign> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> loculus marmoreus </quote></cit> <ref cRef="Sx. Hed." loc="16">Sx. Hed. 16</ref>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ንፍቅ፡ ዘአፍራጽ፡ ዘውእቱ፡ ርኳም፡</foreign> <ref cRef="Sx. Hed." loc="17">Sx. Hed. 17</ref>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጻሕል፡ ዘእብነ፡ ርኳም፡</foreign> <ref cRef="Sx. Masc." loc="10">Sx. Masc. 10</ref>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ምድሩ፡ ለቍድስ፡ ኮነ፡ ርኳመ፡ ወደመ፡ ቅቱላን፡ ይረግዕ፡ ላዕለ፡ ርኳም፡ ወኢይየብስ፡</foreign> <ref cRef="Jsp." loc="356">Jsp. p. 356</ref>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">መካን፡ ፅፍፁፍ፡ በርኳም፡ ወደሙ፡ ልቡጥ፡ ውስቴቱ፡</foreign> <ref cRef="Jsp." loc="302">Jsp. p. 302</ref>; <ref cRef="Jsp." loc="355.">Jsp. p. 355.</ref> – <lbl expand="Vocabularium Aethiopicum, -a -a">Voc. Ae.</lbl>: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ርኳም፡ ብ፡ እብነ፡ በረድ፡</foreign>; <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote> aliud </quote></cit>: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ርክም፡</foreign> (v. <foreign xml:lang="gez">ርኳም፡</foreign>) <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዘ፡ ሣፁን።</foreign> (male). </sense>
               
            <sense xml:id="Tmain" xml:lang="en" source="#traces"> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote>rǝkʷām</quote></cit>, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሩካም፡</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote>rukām</quote></cit> <sense n="G" xml:id="TG"> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ርኳም፡</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote>rǝkʷām</quote></cit> «<cit type="translation" xml:lang="fr"><quote>caisse</quote></cit>» ― <foreign xml:lang="am">ሣጥን፡</foreign> Ms. <ref type="BM" target="BNFabb217">BNFabb217</ref>, fol. 60v. <lb/>
 <bibl><ptr target="bm:Grebaut1952SuppLexicon"/><citedRange unit="page"> 155</citedRange></bibl> 
</sense> <sense n="L" xml:id="TL"> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ርኳም</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote>rǝkʷām</quote></cit>, (Lt) <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሩካም</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote>rukām</quote></cit> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><quote>marble</quote></cit> <lb/>
 <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሮኩም፡</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote>rokum</quote></cit> (<bibl><ptr target="bm:AlaqaTayya1965MSawasew"/></bibl>, <bibl><ptr target="bm:daMag1953"/></bibl>), <foreign xml:lang="gez">ርክም፡</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote>rǝkm</quote></cit> (Sw. in <bibl><ptr target="bm:Dillmann1865Lexicon"/><citedRange unit="page"> 300</citedRange></bibl>) = Amh. <foreign xml:lang="am">ሳጽን</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote>saṣǝn</quote></cit> ‘chest, coffer’; probably comes from an expression such as <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሳጹነ፡</foreign> (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ሳጽነ፡</foreign>) <foreign xml:lang="gez">ርኳም</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote>sāṣuna (sāṣǝna) rǝkʷām</quote></cit> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><quote>chest of marble</quote></cit> (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ንፍቀ፡ ርኳም</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote>nǝfqa rǝkʷām</quote></cit> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><quote>coffin of marble</quote></cit>) and does not mean ‘chest, coffer’ by itself <lb/>
 <bibl><ptr target="bm:Leslau1987dic"/><citedRange unit="page"> 470a</citedRange></bibl> 
</sense> </sense></entry>
